        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Swink, or over La Junta, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and brief penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Junta, North La Junta, Swink, Cheraw, and Blue Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
